==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stage manager
<hw>Stage manager</hw>. <fld>(Theat.)</fld> <def>One in control of the
stage during the production of a play. He directs the stage hands,
property man, etc., has charge of all details behind the curtain, except
the acting, and has a general oversight of the actors. Sometimes he is
also the <er>stage director</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stageplay</ent>⟦br⟧
